WEBVTT

1
00:03:32.423 --> 00:03:35.176
Wake up, come on.
We're in Milan.


2
00:03:36.092 --> 00:03:38.345
Get up, Luca, we're here.

3
00:03:40.972 --> 00:03:41.972
At last!

4
00:03:45.602 --> 00:03:46.853
Come on, Mamma.

5
00:03:49.606 --> 00:03:50.732
Are you tired?

6
00:04:00.367 --> 00:04:02.201
Rocco, the basket.

7
00:04:17.008 --> 00:04:18.552
Ma, got everything?

8
00:04:19.177 --> 00:04:22.095
- You tired?
- You're sure you have everything?


9
00:04:22.096 --> 00:04:24.891
- Where's Vincenzo?
- I don't know.


10
00:04:25.016 --> 00:04:28.226
- Why isn't he here yet?
- Maybe he's outside.


11
00:04:28.227 --> 00:04:30.730
Why isn't Vincenzo here?

12
00:04:31.940 --> 00:04:35.568
- Why isn't Vincenzo here?
- I can't see, you look.


13
00:04:35.569 --> 00:04:36.569
Here!

14
00:04:39.113 --> 00:04:41.074
Ma, want me to look for him?

15
00:04:41.074 --> 00:04:43.076
- Don't get lost.
- Sure!


16
00:04:59.426 --> 00:05:01.010
There's nobody here.

17
00:05:46.348 --> 00:05:47.474
How beautiful!

18
00:05:51.603 --> 00:05:54.731
- Ciro, look how nice!
- Big, isn't it?


19
00:05:59.278 --> 00:06:01.237
What a city!

20
00:06:04.115 --> 00:06:07.244
Rocco, look at those
shops, the lights.


21
00:06:08.953 --> 00:06:10.497
It's like daylight.

22
00:06:11.080 --> 00:06:12.081
Listen!

23
00:06:15.794 --> 00:06:18.297
What stop is near this address?

24
00:06:18.463 --> 00:06:21.132
- Last stop.
- Last stop?


25
00:06:21.383 --> 00:06:24.385
Last stop, end of the line.
At Lambrate.


26
00:06:24.386 --> 00:06:27.180
- What then?
- Get off at Lambrate.


27
00:06:28.932 --> 00:06:30.600
- My son.
- Your son?


28
00:06:30.809 --> 00:06:33.143
- The oldest...
- Oh, the oldest.


29
00:06:33.144 --> 00:06:35.314
We're going to see him.

30
00:06:37.772 --> 00:06:40.775
Let's toast the fiancés!

31
00:06:40.984 --> 00:06:43.069
Best wishes! All the best!

32
00:06:46.365 --> 00:06:50.702
One always ends up drinking
too much at these parties.


33
00:06:52.871 --> 00:06:53.872
Here we are!

34
00:06:55.332 --> 00:06:56.791
Thank you, thanks.

35
00:06:57.709 --> 00:06:59.794
They decided on their own.

36
00:07:00.545 --> 00:07:02.797
Parents don't count anymore.

37
00:07:04.591 --> 00:07:06.968
We had to start sometime.

38
00:07:08.762 --> 00:07:12.682
Besides, I don't feel
like going back down there.


39
00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:16.686
I want to raise my family up here.

40
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:20.231
Why don't you get married too?

41
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:23.527
Me? Only my sister's that dumb.

42
00:07:30.033 --> 00:07:32.702
He's worried about supporting us.

43
00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:35.330
But we'll manage on our own.

44
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:38.375
- That's right.
- Right, Vincenzo?


45
00:07:41.378 --> 00:07:42.378
Thanks.

46
00:07:50.679 --> 00:07:54.139
- We're not looking for anything.
- Oh, Lord! Please...


47
00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:55.183
This is Aldo.

48
00:07:56.225 --> 00:07:58.144
I'm going to the movies.

49
00:07:59.228 --> 00:08:01.398
- Have fun!
- Bye!


50
00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:05.652
- Bye, Ma.
- Bye. Have fun.


51
00:08:07.446 --> 00:08:08.822
Thank you.

52
00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:12.366
Always the movies!
He lives on bread and movies.


53
00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:14.369
It's a fixation with him!

54
00:08:14.411 --> 00:08:16.830
Sunday I went along too..

55
00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:19.458
And immediately fell asleep.

56
00:08:21.626 --> 00:08:24.713
Hello.
Do the Giannellis live here?


57
00:08:25.714 --> 00:08:27.799
I'm Mrs. Parondi.

58
00:08:28.300 --> 00:08:30.468
Vincenzo,
come and see who's here.


59
00:08:30.469 --> 00:08:33.221
- Come in, come in.
- Thank you.


60
00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:36.558
Mamma!

61
00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:40.895
Oh, my son.

62
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.360
Luca, how are you?

63
00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:52.824
Rosaria, dear Rosaria.

64
00:08:55.034 --> 00:08:58.955
Your family?
Oh, God bless you!


65
00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:02.041
This is Rosaria, everybody.

66
00:09:03.335 --> 00:09:05.086
They're your brothers?

67
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:07.464
- This is Luca.
- Hello.


68
00:09:07.756 --> 00:09:09.924
Simone. She's my fiancé.

69
00:09:10.133 --> 00:09:12.302
- Good.
- Rocco..


70
00:09:12.511 --> 00:09:14.095
And Ciro.
- Hello.


71
00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:16.764
Leave everything here
and come inside.


72
00:09:16.765 --> 00:09:17.765
Come on.

73
00:09:20.184 --> 00:09:21.184
Come inside.

74
00:09:22.854 --> 00:09:25.106
It's her, Vincenzo's mother!

75
00:09:25.274 --> 00:09:28.985
What a long trip.
Offer her some wine.


76
00:09:29.486 --> 00:09:31.446
Come on, boys!

77
00:09:34.408 --> 00:09:38.328
Offer them some wine,
they must be freezing.


78
00:09:38.620 --> 00:09:42.164
Handsome boys, huh?
The picture of their mother.


79
00:09:42.165 --> 00:09:44.793
Ginetta, pass the cookies around.

80
00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:47.837
Really handsome boys.
Tired, huh?


81
00:09:48.713 --> 00:09:51.300
It's true, they're very similar.

82
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:54.928
They're dead tired.
Such a long trip!


83
00:09:55.094 --> 00:09:59.140
- What a nice surprise!
- What's in there?


84
00:10:00.392 --> 00:10:03.853
What misfortune
came upon us, my dear son!


85
00:10:10.485 --> 00:10:11.528
What is this?

86
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:14.405
Don't you wear mourning
for your father?


87
00:10:14.406 --> 00:10:15.406
No,..

88
00:10:15.699 --> 00:10:17.242
It's just that...

89
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:21.745
She's Ginetta. I wrote you
about our engagement.


90
00:10:21.746 --> 00:10:25.500
You arrived
just in time to bless us.


91
00:10:25.709 --> 00:10:26.709
Marriage?

92
00:10:27.419 --> 00:10:31.255
You're so rich that you
can marry? Especially now..


93
00:10:31.256 --> 00:10:34.634
With your whole family
depending on you?


94
00:10:34.968 --> 00:10:37.178
If only you'd written..

95
00:10:37.387 --> 00:10:40.098
And let me know!
- We did write!


96
00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:43.935
Yes, but that was
when Papa died.


97
00:10:44.769 --> 00:10:49.524
I answered: "First I have
to find them a job".


98
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:52.902
It's not that easy here in Milan.

99
00:10:53.152 --> 00:10:56.071
- Have a seat.
- Make yourselves comfortable.


100
00:10:56.072 --> 00:10:59.242
- Tell us about yourselves.
- Let's hear.


101
00:10:59.243 --> 00:11:01.661
Make yourself at home.

102
00:11:02.161 --> 00:11:05.249
- He's shy.
- Probably tired.


103
00:11:06.124 --> 00:11:08.876
- Not really.
- No? Naturally, he's young.


104
00:11:08.877 --> 00:11:10.754
Were you cold?

105
00:11:11.170 --> 00:11:12.881
- No.
- Some candy?


106
00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:17.802
And what have you got there?

107
00:11:18.094 --> 00:11:19.012
Oranges.

108
00:11:19.013 --> 00:11:22.098
Amelia!
Oranges from our hometown.


109
00:11:22.266 --> 00:11:24.976
- Would you like one?
- Thank you.


110
00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:28.355
Just smell!

111
00:11:30.315 --> 00:11:31.315
Thank you.

112
00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:36.445
Listen, Rosaria, I thought
you came for their engagement.


113
00:11:36.446 --> 00:11:41.576
And that Vincenzo said nothing
because he wanted to surprise us.


114
00:11:43.287 --> 00:11:46.831
My heart's too heavy
to think about parties.


115
00:11:46.956 --> 00:11:50.377
And now what?
You came here straight..


116
00:11:50.585 --> 00:11:52.671
From the station?
- Yes.


117
00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:56.550
So where
are you gonna sleep tonight?


118
00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:01.513
My son won't leave us
in the street.


119
00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.308
He'll take care of us.

120
00:12:05.183 --> 00:12:08.353
Listen here, Rosaria.

121
00:12:08.937 --> 00:12:13.231
I can understand your being
worried about your boys,..


122
00:12:13.232 --> 00:12:16.235
But what about my girl, huh?!

123
00:12:18.905 --> 00:12:22.616
She arrives just like that,
and ruins everything!


124
00:12:22.617 --> 00:12:25.494
- Mamma, what are you saying?
- Mamma's right.


125
00:12:25.495 --> 00:12:28.247
- You don't understand.
- I'm nobody's fool.


126
00:12:28.248 --> 00:12:30.249
- There's no need to shout!
- Mamma's right!


127
00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:33.419
Let's get out of this house!
Rocco! Simone!


128
00:12:33.420 --> 00:12:36.256
- Mamma, no!
- You're all crazy!


129
00:12:36.423 --> 00:12:41.093
- Come to your mother.
- I'm not crazy. I've understood, all right.


130
00:12:41.094 --> 00:12:44.848
They want to keep you
from helping your mother.


131
00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:49.060
They've no respect
for your dead father! Heathens!


132
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:50.812
How dare you!

133
00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:54.232
- Let's get out!
- No, no.


134
00:12:54.399 --> 00:12:57.235
Quiet, you, you're one of them!

135
00:12:57.652 --> 00:13:00.113
Let's, boys, hurry up!

136
00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:06.076
God will punish you,
for He judges everyone.


137
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.162
No, wait. They didn't mean
to offend you.


138
00:13:09.163 --> 00:13:12.166
- Move it.
- Leave me, leave me!


139
00:13:12.376 --> 00:13:15.878
- You keep quiet, jerk!
- Think I'm afraid, do you?


140
00:13:15.879 --> 00:13:18.172
Leave my house!

141
00:13:18.632 --> 00:13:22.261
Hear that? What are you
waiting for? Come on!


142
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:24.721
Get out!

143
00:13:32.729 --> 00:13:33.729
Armando!

144
00:13:37.359 --> 00:13:40.529
- Armando!
- Who is it?


145
00:13:43.156 --> 00:13:45.450
It's Vincenzo.
Let me in.


146
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:51.122
What's wrong?
How come so late?


147
00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:52.874
I'll explain later.

148
00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:55.460
Hurry up! It's cold!

149
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:03.593
So why are you here
at this hour?


150
00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:06.763
To sleep, if possible.

151
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:09.474
It's almost day already.

152
00:14:09.683 --> 00:14:12.602
Let's hear, boy,
what've you done?


153
00:14:12.769 --> 00:14:14.771
I can explain everything.

154
00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:16.940
Down!

155
00:14:18.733 --> 00:14:21.820
Come on in.
You're afraid of the dogs?


156
00:14:22.279 --> 00:14:25.907
Here there's wood, a stove,
all the comforts!


157
00:14:28.785 --> 00:14:30.245
So explain.

158
00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:35.792
My whole family arrived
unexpectedly, like an earthquake..


159
00:14:36.167 --> 00:14:39.463
And then argued
with my future in-laws.


160
00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:44.551
I had to give up my room,
my fiancé and everything.


161
00:14:45.927 --> 00:14:49.973
For you, a room and a fiancé
are the same thing?


162
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:53.226
- It's no joke.
- No.


163
00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:55.978
How can I support
my whole family?


164
00:14:55.979 --> 00:14:58.898
Where'll they stay?

165
00:14:59.107 --> 00:15:01.233
I managed something for tonight,..

166
00:15:01.234 --> 00:15:03.987
But tomorrow?
Good God!


167
00:15:04.237 --> 00:15:09.743
What's the problem?
Milan's full of empty houses.


168
00:15:10.201 --> 00:15:14.289
Apartment buildings are
shooting up like mushrooms.


169
00:15:14.664 --> 00:15:16.250
What about the rent?

170
00:15:16.875 --> 00:15:20.504
Listen to me, do what all
you Southerners do.


171
00:15:20.587 --> 00:15:23.046
- Know what I mean?
- Not exactly.


172
00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:26.343
You rent a public housing
apartment and..


173
00:15:26.551 --> 00:15:28.678
If you can, you pay.

174
00:15:28.887 --> 00:15:31.472
But after a few months
you stop paying.


175
00:15:31.473 --> 00:15:33.350
- How is that?
- Wait!


176
00:15:33.558 --> 00:15:36.311
A month later they evict you.

177
00:15:36.561 --> 00:15:38.397
- How can I...
- Wait!


178
00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:42.316
Then you join
the other evictees where you pay..


179
00:15:42.317 --> 00:15:45.569
Almost nothing and there's
central heating, electricity, etc.


180
00:15:45.570 --> 00:15:49.949
Milan's City Hall
leaves no one on the street.


181
00:15:50.242 --> 00:15:52.618
Couldn't we go straight there?

182
00:15:52.619 --> 00:15:55.121
No, you have to be evicted.

183
00:15:55.747 --> 00:15:58.749
- Ah, right!
- That's the secret, understand?


184
00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:02.421
- Good evening.
- Don't be such a knucklehead!


185
00:16:17.018 --> 00:16:18.102
Porter!

186
00:16:20.564 --> 00:16:21.773
Porter!

187
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:23.358
Huh?

188
00:16:23.858 --> 00:16:26.403
I'm Mrs. Parondi, open up!

189
00:16:26.695 --> 00:16:30.907
I'm coming! Hold on!

190
00:16:32.451 --> 00:16:35.995
- What's the big rush?!
- Is this the place?


191
00:16:36.204 --> 00:16:39.123
- There.
- I'm Rosaria Parondi.


192
00:16:39.333 --> 00:16:42.711
Yes, Parondi, it's over there.

193
00:16:42.961 --> 00:16:45.380
Downstairs, lower level.

194
00:16:46.005 --> 00:16:47.549
Get a load of them.

195
00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.609
Good morning, Signora Maria.

196
00:17:06.610 --> 00:17:09.903
Did you see those dreadful people?
Zulus!


197
00:17:09.904 --> 00:17:12.531
- Where are they from?
- Lucania.


198
00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:15.158
Lucania? Odd name! Where's that?
Never heard of it.


199
00:17:15.159 --> 00:17:16.953
Down South.

200
00:17:17.120 --> 00:17:20.457
Ahh!
The land of do-nothings!


201
00:18:06.878 --> 00:18:08.672
Wake up!

202
00:18:09.339 --> 00:18:10.339
Ciro.

203
00:18:10.382 --> 00:18:11.841
It's snowing.

204
00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:14.969
Rocco!
There's work for everybody.


205
00:18:15.219 --> 00:18:17.639
Simone! It's snowing.

206
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.311
What happened?

207
00:18:22.561 --> 00:18:24.895
Nothing.
Today there's work for us.


208
00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:25.896
The snow.

209
00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.482
It's sticking to the ground!

210
00:18:28.483 --> 00:18:31.570
Luca, look, it's snowing.

211
00:18:31.861 --> 00:18:33.905
- The snow!
- Get up.


212
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:37.116
Move along or we'll be too late.

213
00:18:38.535 --> 00:18:42.372
The Milanese don't like
their streets with snow.


214
00:18:42.747 --> 00:18:44.666
Hey, sleepyhead, get up!

215
00:18:48.169 --> 00:18:50.297
Look at the snow!

216
00:18:52.799 --> 00:18:55.093
Simone, darling, get up.

217
00:18:55.552 --> 00:18:57.804
It's snowing!
How wonderful!


218
00:18:57.929 --> 00:19:00.389
There should be work
for everybody.


219
00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:04.519
Look, the others are almost ready!

220
00:19:04.853 --> 00:19:07.689
Get up, get up!

221
00:19:08.690 --> 00:19:11.734
- Get a move on, Rocco.
- We're coming.


222
00:19:11.735 --> 00:19:12.861
Simone!

223
00:19:16.615 --> 00:19:18.617
Rocco, you've been sick.

224
00:19:18.992 --> 00:19:23.288
- Wear one of my sweaters.
- But it's a woman's.


225
00:19:25.039 --> 00:19:28.959
Let them tease away. Listen
to your mother. Put it on.


226
00:19:28.960 --> 00:19:31.129
I'll get some breakfast.

227
00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:33.882
Simone!

228
00:19:34.716 --> 00:19:37.677
Come on, Simone,
we're working today.


229
00:19:37.927 --> 00:19:41.556
- Luca!
- Luca, you'll make us late. Quit it!


230
00:19:43.475 --> 00:19:46.353
- Careful not to fall.
- Off you go!


231
00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:50.274
- Hurry, boys!
- Move it, Ciro! Simone!


232
00:19:50.482 --> 00:19:54.110
- The coffee's almost ready.
- Here I am.


233
00:19:54.361 --> 00:19:58.823
Drink the eggs,
they're fresh and healthy!


234
00:20:02.118 --> 00:20:05.872
The coffee's boiling hot.
Put in lots of bread.


235
00:20:06.415 --> 00:20:08.833
Fix some for your brother too.

236
00:20:12.337 --> 00:20:15.714
Oh, thank God,
there's work here for everybody!


237
00:20:15.715 --> 00:20:19.093
The Lord is merciful.
He sent us the snow.


238
00:20:19.261 --> 00:20:21.804
- You wearing my sweater?
- Yes.


239
00:20:21.805 --> 00:20:28.437
Simone, dear, hurry. Come on!

240
00:20:28.645 --> 00:20:32.565
- Poor baby, he has to go to work.
- It's freezing. You even left..


241
00:20:32.566 --> 00:20:36.695
The window open.
I don't get hot flashes.


242
00:20:46.496 --> 00:20:50.166
Come on, the city's waiting
for us, lazybones!


243
00:20:51.209 --> 00:20:54.670
That guy will never change.
Finish your coffee.


244
00:20:54.671 --> 00:20:58.007
I'll get lunch ready.
Luca, my satchel!


245
00:20:58.425 --> 00:21:01.010
- Yes, Mamma.
- No, I'll get it.


246
00:21:04.138 --> 00:21:07.850
- Luca, my satchel!
- It's here, under the bed.


247
00:21:07.851 --> 00:21:14.566
- I'll get it for you.
- Hurry up!


248
00:21:17.569 --> 00:21:21.323
Here are your coats.

249
00:21:21.656 --> 00:21:24.408
Rocco, cover up.
Don't take chances,..


250
00:21:24.409 --> 00:21:26.869
You've been sick.
If you had a chill...


251
